Now administrator have to go to every single project and add it to project category.

I think that it will be eaiser if multiple projects can be added to single category on "View Project Categories" page.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
*NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3406].
{panel}
*Original request description*

Instead of having just a simple linear comment tree, how about being able to have an (optional) threaded view where replies to comments and replies to replies could be seen as such.

The option to allow threaded comments, linear comments or even comments at all could be on an issue by issue basis as well as having project / global defaults which you could fall back on (if unselected).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3400].
  {panel}

Having successfully got the CVS Log integration working again for the XDoclet JIRA, I noticed that there were a number of mail messages accumulating in the relevant POP3 account.  This is because the CVS commit logs are mailed to the developer's mailing list, and the other messages on the list aren't processed by the CVS Log (or any other) MessageHandler.  However, the mailbox in question has a 20 Meg limit, and at some point in the future it will start bouncing messages if nothing is done to delete the extra messages.  It would be nice, therefore, if there was a MessageHandler which deleted all the messages older than a specified number of days, so I could set up a service to clear out the surplus ones.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3385].
  {panel}

After configuring a new POP3/IMAP server, it would be useful to be able to check that I've typed in the password etc. correctly.  In addition to the Edit & Del links, an option to Test a connection (which would login to the server, possibly list any available messages, then disconnect) would enable this.  Otherwise, I have to wait for the CVS log integration (or other service that uses it) to work (or not) in order to know if I've got it configured right.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
