  {panel}

I like to have due-dates/scheduled release dates for versions. It helps us (using a tight schedule) in knowing when all issues of a certain release should be fixed.

When creating a version, add a description of what is going to be in that release (i.e. improve usability, add release notes), so people know what is coming.

I'm attempting to use the calendar date picker when creating a new issue.  The popup appears as expected, but when rolling over dates, the area below the calendar gets filled with text like "function (match, par) {return s[par];}, function (match, par) {return s[par];}, ...".  If I choose a date, the "due date" field is filled with 

function (match, par) 
{
  return s[par];
}-function (match, par) 
{
  return s[par];
}-function (match, par) 
{
  return s[par];
}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3330].
  {panel}

We have a JIRA installation with about 20 projects. 4 of them is in a project category. This category is shown normaly when having the "Projects" portlet on the dashboard. But I have customized my dashboard so I only see the projects that I'm a developer on (about 8). I'm also a developer on all of the 4 projects in the project category. But because I'm using 8 "Project" portlets I'm not seeing any project category.

It would be nice if the project category feature also would display when using the "Project" portlets.

Of cause I can imagine that some people would not like this feature. So maybe it should be possible to select if project categories should be shown or not. I'm not sure how this should be done - maybe in the users profile or by using a special portlet?
